cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the concept of interference temperature (IT) and applies it to transform the EE boundary characterization problem into a set of fractional concave programming problems. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses coordinated beamforming in multi-cell MISO systems, which is a networking and communication problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a decentralized algorithm to implement the multi-cell coordinated beamforming, which falls under the domain of control systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper considers the achievable data rate at the MS, which is a multimedia-related metric. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper characterizes the Pareto boundary of the achievable energy efficiency (EE) region of the K links, which is a game-theoretic concept.
